frameDefinitions: A Speaker uses as a Label to refer to an Entity.
A Protagonist delays a planned action because they cannot or do not want to proceed until an Expected_event occurs.
A Speaker conventionally uses a particular Term to refer to an Entity.
A  Counter_actor or Cause  impedes an Agent in an Activity or impedes the unfolding or continuation of a State_of_affairs.
This frame presents a situation where there is a certain Number of instances of an Entity or a certain Number that quantifies a Unit.
A Speaker uses a particular linguistic form, a Name to refer to an Entity.

listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Speaker</fen> is the person who conventionally uses a linguistic sign to refer to an <fen>Entity</fen>.
The concrete or abstract thing with which the <fen>Speaker</fen> has associated a particular linguistic sign.
The linguistic sign that the <fen>Speaker</fen> uses to designate the <fen>Entity</fen>.
A text whose author applies a particular <fen>Label</fen> to an <fen>Entity</fen>.
A time period in which a <fen>Speaker</fen> uses the <fen>Label</fen>.
A physical space whose occupants use the <fen>Label</fen> to refer to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The sentient being who cannot proceed with their planned activities until a Salient_entity has arrived or an Expected_event has occurred.
A concrete or abstract entity that the <fen>Protagonist</fen> expects to participate in an <fen>Expected_event</fen>, typically that of arriving at the <fen>Place</fen> of the <fen>Protagonist</fen>.
The <fen>Expected_event</fen> is an event that needs to take place or a state that needs to begin to hold before the <fen>Protagonist</fen> can proceed with their planned activities.
The time period during which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is waiting.
The location in which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is waiting.
The type of <fen>Entity</fen> that is conventionally referred to by a <fen>Term</fen>.
The linguistic sign that is used for referring to a type of <fen>Entity</fen>.
The speaker or speech community that uses a <fen>Term</fen> to refer to a particular <fen>Entity</fen>.
An event or state_of_Affairs that successfully impedes an <fen>Agent</fen> or a State_of_affairs.
A person who intentionally or not acts in such a way that an <fen>Agent</fen> or State_of_affairs is impeded.
A person who is intentionally engaged in some <fen>Activity</fen> and who is impeded in that <fen>Activity</fen>.
An <fen>Activity</fen> that is being impeded.
A state or event that is ongoing and whose continuance or unfolding is impeded.
The time at which the <fen>Counter_actor</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen> works agains the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Counter_actor</fen> subverts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Number</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Entity</fen> enumerated by the <fen>Number</fen>.

A <fen>Unit</fen> expresses some quantification of some property of an entity, event, or situation by providing a base value of the property combined with a <fen>Number</fen> expressing how the current value for the property relates to the <fen>Unit</fen>.
The person who uses the <fen>Name</fen>  to refer to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The entity that is designated by the <fen>Speaker</fen> with the <fen>Name</fen> used.
The linguistic form used by the <fen>Speaker</fen> to refer to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The point of time or interval when the <fen>Speaker</fen> uses the <fen>Name</fen>.
